It&#8217;s understood the pair left a retailer after collecting money when they were held up by four robbers. CAPE TOWN - Two security guards have been seriously wounded during a cash-in-transit heist in Port Elizabeth on Thursday morning.It s understood the pair left a retailer after collecting money when they were held up by four robbers.Trauma Net paramedic Dean Slater says the robbers allegedly fled the scene with an undisclosed amount of cash and two firearms. This morning, trauma paramedics attended to a cash-in-transit heist on Commercial Road, near the Pick n Pay in Port Elizabeth. Upon arrival the paramedics found that two guards had been shot multiple times. They are currently in a critical but stable condition. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)